oc:kn_0c088277 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating any proposed BGP fix for Azure Virtual WAN" ;
    oc:directiveContent "BGP sessions between hubs cannot be administratively disabled by customers — they are owned by Azure's shared control plane." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Azure's connectivity SLA and shared infrastructure depend on BGP sessions remaining active; customers control routing policy, not session existence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_0e67b343 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Before beginning any analysis" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Verify all ASNs referenced in preferences.json, relationships.json, route.json, and route_leaks.json exist in topology.json; verify relationship symmetry holds." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Invalid or inconsistent inputs produce meaningless analysis results." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0f8a9766 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assessing oscillation mitigation proposals" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Timer tuning or dampening does NOT fix BGP oscillation — it only reduces symptoms without breaking preference cycles." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Oscillation is caused by preference cycles in route selection; adjusting timers masks the problem but the cycle persists." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_66980e51 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting a fix strategy" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prefer fixes in this order: Tier 1 (Routing Intent) > Tier 2 (Export/Route Policy) > Tier 3 (UDR). Routing intent decouples forwarding from BGP stability; UDR only masks control-plane issues." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Routing intent operates above BGP making forwarding deterministic; export policy is protocol-correct; UDR is a data-plane mask that leaves control-plane problems unresolved." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_6aeb427b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When assessing route leak mitigation proposals" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Accepting fewer prefixes does NOT prevent route leaks — ingress filtering alone doesn't stop export of other leaked routes." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Route leaks are caused by valley-free export violations; limiting ingress prefixes doesn't constrain export behavior." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_80c39daf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Always, when proposing any Azure BGP fix" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Problems must be fixed using routing policy (routing intent, export policy, communities, UDR, ingress filtering), not topology destruction." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Cloud providers separate policy control from connectivity existence to protect shared infrastructure and SLAs." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_aad0cfca a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When detecting oscillation in preference graphs" ;
    oc:directiveContent "A 2-node preference cycle (A prefers B, B prefers A) is sufficient to conclude BGP oscillation exists." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Even minimal cycles cause indefinite route flapping between the two participants." .

oc:kn_ada7587f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When producing analysis output" ;
    oc:directiveContent """1. Identification: oscillation detected (preference cycle) and/or route leak detected (valley-free violation)
2. Root cause explanation: which ASNs form the cycle or which edges violate valley-free
3. Recommended fix: Tier 1 (routing intent) > Tier 2 (export policy) > Tier 3 (UDR) with specific mechanism
4. Rejected fixes: explicit rejection of any prohibited fixes with Azure-specific reasoning""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "oscillation_result",
        "recommended_tier",
        "rejected_fixes",
        "root_cause",
        "route_leak_result" .

oc:kn_bb11df96 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When evaluating any proposed BGP fix for Azure Virtual WAN" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Peering connections cannot be shut down or removed as a fix — this breaks all other traffic running on the connections." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Connectivity removal is topology destruction, not policy correction; it violates Azure's separation of policy control from connectivity existence." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_bf1a419a a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When detecting BGP preference cycles to diagnose oscillation" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
    oc:directiveContent """pref = {asn: prefer_via_asn, ...}

def find_cycle(start):
    path = []
    seen = {}
    cur = start
    while cur in pref:
        if cur in seen:
            return path[seen[cur]:]  # cycle found
        seen[cur] = len(path)
        path.append(cur)
        cur = pref[cur]
    return None""" .

oc:kn_de7ebfc4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When analyzing any Azure BGP problem" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Sanity-check inputs: verify every ASN exists in topology.json and relationship symmetry holds (provider(A→B) ⇔ customer(B→A), peer symmetric). 2. Detect oscillation: build directed graph ASN→preferred next-hop, find cycles. 3. Detect route leaks: check if provider-learned or peer-learned routes are exported to peers/providers. 4. Classify proposed fixes as allowed (policy-level) or prohibited (connectivity destruction)." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_f3fdec81 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RollbackProcedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a policy fix has unintended side effects" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a fix causes unexpected behavior, revert to Tier 3 (UDR) for immediate containment while investigating, as UDR provides deterministic data-plane control independent of BGP." .

